msgid ""
"All of the precision controls detailed on the page can be combined with the "
":doc:`Axis Locking "
"</getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/axis_locking>` "
"controls and used with the different :doc:`Pivot Points "
"</getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/pivot_point/index>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/precision.rst:56
msgid "Holding CTRL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/precision.rst:59
#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/precision.rst:111
msgid "Grab/move transformations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/precision.rst:63
msgid "1 Blender Unit - shown at the default zoom level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/precision.rst:66
msgid ""
"For grab/move operations at the default zoom level, holding :kbd:`Ctrl` will"
" cause your selection to move by increments of 1 Blender Unit (1 BU) (i.e. "
"between the two light grey lines). Zooming in enough to see the next set of "
"grey lines will now cause :kbd:`Ctrl` movements to occur by 1/10 of a BU. "
"Zooming in further until the next set of grey lines becomes visible will "
"cause movement to happen by 1/100 of a BU and so on until the zoom limit is "
"reached. Zooming out will have the opposite effect and cause movement to "
"happen by increments of 10, 100 etc BU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/transformations/transform_control/precision.rst:75
msgid ""
":doc:`Read more about Zooming "
"</getting_started/basics/navigating/3d_view#zooming_the_view>`"
msgstr ""

